          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The triple gamma coincidence technique",
                " with Gammasphere."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GE-IN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 72 Compton suppressed Ge detectors"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SI",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The energy spectrum of charged",
                "particles was measured by using two deltaE-E Si",
                "detector telescopes installed at the center of the",
                "Gammasphere array at Argonne National Laboratory.",
                "Each deltaE-E telescope included one deltaE detector",
                " (of 15 mu-m thickness and 10x10 mm2 area) and one",
                "strip detector. The strip detectors were 400 mu-m and",
                "60x60 mm2 in thickness and area, respectively and had",
                "29 strips. With the position resolution of the strip",
                "detector (4 mm wide strips and 1 mm resolution along",
                "each strip) , the deltaE-E telescopes provided",
                "unambiguous Z and A identification for all the light",
                "charged particles of interest. The energy calibration",
                "of the telescopes was performed with 224Ra and 228Th",
                "radioactive sources. This calibration automatically",
                "takes the presence of the Mylar foil into account. A",
                "software correction was applied for the energy loss",
                "in the Au foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 252Cf source with a strength of the order of 30",
                "mu-Ci was sandwiched between two Au foils, each 19",
                "mg/cm2 in thickness. These foils were used to stop",
                "the fission fragments so that problems associated",
                "with the Doppler shift of prompt fission gamma-rays",
                "were minimized. In addition, on each side of the",
                "source a 0.84 mg/cm2 Mylar foil was added to provide",
                "full absorption of a particles emitted in the",
                "radioactive decay of 252Cf."
              ]
            }
          ],
